<potuz0> Even if everything goes wrong and you never see any IL, what is the problem/complication that you are seeing? I am giving very concrete examples of advantages to decoupling them. There is one concrete advantage of coupling them that I see in that you can synchronously set the forkchoice node and you know that the IL was valid when you imported the block, other than that I see the list of advantages to decoupling vastly outweigh this: 
- Better pipelining (can use CPU and broadcast 10 seconds before your slot)
- Lighter blocks (you don't need to send the IL with them and you don't need to validate it at the same time as the payload)
- Better gossip validation (you do not need to enter the message to check that it was a block that you already imported) 
- Better Builder API (no changes) 

I would agree with you that falling back to RPC to request the IL would actually make me think twice, but if you don't I don't see how the list above is not contundent
